cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.THEORY 

This paper deals with regular expressions and finite state automata, which are fundamental concepts in formal language theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the construction of a deterministic automaton, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the use of marking positions in the regular expression suggests a connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper's focus on the effectiveness of combining different techniques suggests a connection to cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science).
